OL,3,CSchoolboy waited for pupils to sleep
OL,4,Cbefore alleged hammer attack, court
OL,5,Ctold
OL,7,F"The defendant was awake, and he
OL,8,Fdecided to put into action a plan that
OL,9,Fhe had been fermenting in his head for
OL,10,Fsome time," Mr Dawes said.
OL,12,F"And that plan was to kill the two
OL,13,Fboys, and he decided to do it whilst
OL,14,Fthey slept in their own beds, and he
OL,15,Fdecided to do it with a hammer.
OL,17,F"It is not known which boy he attacked
OL,18,Ffirst. The defendant was in possession
OL,19,Fof four claw hammers ` a heavy hammer
OL,20,Fwith a flat striking side and two-
OL,21,Fpronged claw at the back.
