OL,5,Ctold
OL,7,F"Mr Roffe-Silvester said he thought
OL,8,Fthe defendant appeared to be 'on a
OL,9,Fmission' and afterwards his face and
OL,10,Fbody relaxed, and he was calm and
OL,11,Fslumped on his feet, squatting against
OL,12,Fthe wall."
OL,14,FAnother student was told to "keep an
OL,15,Feye" on the defendant in the matron's
OL,16,Foffice, Mr Dawes said.
OL,18,F"The defendant told him he was feeling
OL,19,Fquite stressed about things before the
OL,20,Fincident with school tests and owed
OL,21,Fsome money to a girl," he said.
