OL,3,CSchoolboy waited for pupils to sleep
OL,4,Cbefore alleged hammer attack, court
OL,5,Ctold
OL,7,FThe court heard Mr Roffe-Silvester did
OL,8,Fnot realise at first the two boys had
OL,9,Fbeen injured and they were discovered
OL,10,Flying in their beds a few minutes
OL,11,Flater by another student.
OL,13,FMr Dawes told the jury both boys
OL,14,Fsuffered skull fractures, as well as
OL,15,Finjuries to their ribs, spleen, a
OL,16,Fpunctured lung and internal bleeding.
OL,18,F"Blood went everywhere," he said.
