OL,5,Ctold
OL,7,FMr Dawes said both boys are living
OL,8,Fwith the "long-term consequences" of
OL,9,Fthe attack but have no memory of the
OL,10,Fincident.
OL,12,F"Sadly, neither of them will ever be
OL,13,Fthe same again as they were prior to
OL,14,Fthe attack," he said.
OL,16,FThe defendant, now aged 17, denies
OL,17,Fthree charges of attempted murder.
OL,19,FThe trial continues.
